Well, that's what we have arranged.

518
01:48:48.857 --> 01:48:52.319
- If you're sure you wanna do that.
- Oh, yeah, yeah. Yes.

519
01:48:57.115 --> 01:48:59.284
I don't know what I'm gonna say to her.

520
01:49:00.827 --> 01:49:03.079
What in the world am I gonna say to her?

521
01:49:07.125 --> 01:49:09.794
Chuck, Kelly had to let you go.

522
01:49:10.378 --> 01:49:11.379
You know?

523
01:49:12.547 --> 01:49:16.968
She thought you were dead.
And we buried you.

524
01:49:19.971 --> 01:49:23.391
We had a funeral and a coffin, a gravestone.

525
01:49:23.475 --> 01:49:24.809
The whole thing.

526
01:49:26.645 --> 01:49:28.271
You had a coffin?

527
01:49:31.524 --> 01:49:33.068
What was in it?

528
01:49:34.486 --> 01:49:36.696
Well, everybody put something in.

529
01:49:37.364 --> 01:49:41.993
You know, just a cell phone or a beeper, some pictures.

530
01:49:42.244 --> 01:49:44.204
I put in some Elvis CDs.

531
01:49:47.249 --> 01:49:49.167
So you had my funeral,

532
01:49:51.544 --> 01:49:53.838
and then you had Mary's funeral.

533
01:49:58.969 --> 01:50:02.847
Stan, I'm so sorry I wasn't around when Mary died.

534
01:50:05.016 --> 01:50:08.520
I should've been there for you, and I wasn't.

535
01:50:12.941 --> 01:50:14.567
I'm so sorry.

536
01:50:15.527 --> 01:50:20.991
<i>Four years ago, the FedEx family lost five of our sons.</i>

537
01:50:22.033 --> 01:50:24.536
<i>That was a terrible and tragic day.</i>

538
01:50:26.162 --> 01:50:29.040
<i>But today, one of those sons,</i>

539
01:50:29.207 --> 01:50:32.502
<i>Chuck Noland, has been returned to us.</i>

540
01:50:33.378 --> 01:50:35.547
<i>Chuck, welcome home.</i>

541
01:50:44.681 --> 01:50:48.727
<i>Moments ago, Fred Smith welcomed home Chuck Noland.</i>

542
01:50:49.144 --> 01:50:50.145
<i>Michelle?</i>

543
01:50:50.228 --> 01:50:53.481
<i>It's an incredible story, to come back from the dead.</i>

544
01:50:53.565 --> 01:50:56.026
<i>So amazing that Fred Smith welcomed him.</i>

545
01:50:56.109 --> 01:50:58.236
<i>And Fred acknowledged that,</i>

546
01:50:58.320 --> 01:51:00.238
<i>"While time waits for no man,</i>

547
01:51:00.322 --> 01:51:02.991
<i>"we take time to pause
to honour one of our own."</i>

548
01:51:03.074 --> 01:51:05.493
<i>Now, that's an expensive pause.</i>

549
01:51:13.376 --> 01:51:15.378
I'm sorry. I must be in the wrong place.

550
01:51:15.462 --> 01:51:17.255
No, you're in the right place.

551
01:51:18.381 --> 01:51:19.883
You probably don't remember me.

552
01:51:19.966 --> 01:51:22.635
I did root canal on you about five years ago.

553
01:51:23.178 --> 01:51:24.888
Jim Spalding referred you.

554
01:51:27.057 --> 01:51:28.600
Oh, yeah, yeah.

555
01:51:33.772 --> 01:51:35.523
I'm Kelly's husband.

556
01:51:37.359 --> 01:51:38.818
Jerry Lovett.

557
01:51:39.903 --> 01:51:41.154
Kelly wanted...

558
01:51:42.989 --> 01:51:44.783
Kelly wanted to be here...

559
01:51:47.452 --> 01:51:50.080
Look, this is very hard for everyone.

560
01:51:51.790 --> 01:51:54.793
I can't even imagine how hard it is for you.

561
01:51:58.963 --> 01:52:00.173
Kelly...

562
01:52:03.593 --> 01:52:05.303
She's had it rough.

563
01:52:05.470 --> 01:52:09.766
First when she thought she lost you,
now dealing with all of this.

564
01:52:09.974 --> 01:52:11.226
It's confusing.

565
01:52:11.434 --> 01:52:14.270
It's very emotional for her. She's...

566
01:52:17.357 --> 01:52:18.358
She's

567
01:52:19.734 --> 01:52:21.319
sort of lost.

568
01:52:23.321 --> 01:52:25.615
Maybe you could just give her a little more time.

569
01:52:31.162 --> 01:52:32.163
Anyway...

570
01:52:33.706 --> 01:52:35.333
I'm sorry that...

571
01:53:32.932 --> 01:53:34.684
Okay, people, let's go.

572
01:53:34.767 --> 01:53:36.895
Party's over. Let's go home.

573
01:53:37.520 --> 01:53:39.856
You're gonna have to go down at the DMV.

574
01:53:40.356 --> 01:53:42.358
Okay, Maynard, let's go.
Chuck's had a big day.

575
01:53:42.442 --> 01:53:46.279
I have to brief him on his meetings
with the accountants and attorneys.

576
01:53:46.362 --> 01:53:48.656
I will see you bright and early in the morning.

577
01:53:49.157 --> 01:53:52.076
Chuck, welcome home. We love you.

578
01:53:52.160 --> 01:53:53.661
Becca, I need to speak to you.

579
01:53:53.745 --> 01:53:57.040
Chuck, we gotta catch up on some of that fishing, now.

580
01:53:57.248 --> 01:53:58.583
Take care.

581
01:54:01.836 --> 01:54:03.755
- Good night.
- Good night.

582
01:54:07.383 --> 01:54:09.427
You got everything you need?

583
01:54:09.511 --> 01:54:14.015
Okay. If you need anything, sign for it,
and I'll see you in the morning.

584
01:54:14.098 --> 01:54:17.101
Get some sleep.
We got another big day tomorrow.

585
01:54:17.185 --> 01:54:19.938
It takes a lot of paperwork to bring back a man.

586
01:54:21.272 --> 01:54:22.774
Bring you back to life, man.

587
01:54:23.816 --> 01:54:25.693
- Bye, Chuck.
- Take care, now.

588
01:54:25.777 --> 01:54:26.861
Tomorrow.

589
01:54:26.945 --> 01:54:29.447
Tomorrow we're gonna bring you back to life.

590
01:56:14.552 --> 01:56:16.220
How long are you gonna be, man?

591
01:56:18.556 --> 01:56:19.724
Well...

592
01:56:21.309 --> 01:56:24.062
- How long will that buy me?
- About ten minutes.

593
01:56:48.461 --> 01:56:49.796
I'm awake.

594
01:56:50.630 --> 01:56:52.632
I saw your taxi drive up.

595
01:56:55.176 --> 01:56:57.303
Get in here out of the rain.

596
01:57:04.102 --> 01:57:07.855
I saw you down at the hub today,
so I know you were down there.

597
01:57:27.125 --> 01:57:29.043
Let me get you a towel.

598
01:57:40.972 --> 01:57:42.473
They're sleeping.

599
01:57:46.644 --> 01:57:49.981
You'll come in, I'll make you some coffee?

600
01:58:02.410 --> 01:58:04.078
It's a nice house.

601
01:58:04.162 --> 01:58:05.830
Yeah, we got a nice mortgage, too.

602
01:58:14.172 --> 01:58:15.923
What's your daughter's name?

603
01:58:17.008 --> 01:58:18.009
Katie.

604
01:58:19.635 --> 01:58:20.636
Katie.

605
01:58:24.849 --> 01:58:26.601
She's a beautiful little girl.

606
01:58:26.684 --> 01:58:27.977
She's a handful.

607
01:58:42.533 --> 01:58:44.243
Let me get one thing straight.

608
01:58:54.128 --> 01:58:57.507
We have a pro football team now,
but they're in Nashville?

609
01:59:03.471 --> 01:59:06.182
Yeah. Oh, my God. Okay.

610
01:59:06.682 --> 01:59:08.059
They used to be in Houston.

611
01:59:08.601 --> 01:59:11.687
First they were the Oilers, and now they're the Titans.

612
01:59:12.396 --> 01:59:15.066
The Houston Oilers are the Tennessee Titans?

613
01:59:15.566 --> 01:59:18.402
Yeah. But that's not all.

614
01:59:19.028 --> 01:59:21.656
They went to the Super Bowl last year.

615
01:59:22.156 --> 01:59:24.826
- And I missed that.
- You would've died.

616
01:59:24.909 --> 01:59:28.830
They almost won by one yard.
One lousy yard, right at the end.

617
01:59:30.790 --> 01:59:34.168
I got whole milk, 2% and non-fat.

618
01:59:34.252 --> 01:59:37.296
I don't have any half-and-half,
and that's what you like.

619
01:59:37.797 --> 01:59:39.173
That'll do fine.

620
01:59:52.687 --> 01:59:54.939
What happened to you becoming a professor?

621
01:59:57.567 --> 02:00:00.611
You're not Dr Kelly Frears-Lovett?

622
02:00:03.990 --> 02:00:04.991
When you...

623
02:00:06.492 --> 02:00:08.202
When your plane went down,

624
02:00:09.495 --> 02:00:12.039
everything just sort of got put on hold.

625
02:00:14.458 --> 02:00:16.794
I think about taking it up again, though.

626
02:00:29.140 --> 02:00:31.517
I came out here to give you this.

627
02:00:32.685 --> 02:00:34.437
Oh, my God.

628
02:00:36.856 --> 02:00:38.900
I'm sorry it doesn't work.

629
02:00:40.443 --> 02:00:42.820
And I kept the picture.

630
02:00:44.447 --> 02:00:46.407
It was all faded anyway.

631
02:00:47.783 --> 02:00:49.994
I want you to have it. I gave it to you.

632
02:00:50.703 --> 02:00:53.998
That's a family heirloom
and it should stay in your family.

633
02:01:03.674 --> 02:01:07.178
That's everything I have from when you went down to now.

634
02:01:08.763 --> 02:01:11.349
They said they never figured out what caused the crash.

635
02:01:11.682 --> 02:01:15.227
Probably some mislabelled hazardous material caught fire.

636
02:01:18.981 --> 02:01:21.192
So here's where that ship found you.

637
02:01:22.985 --> 02:01:25.363
You drifted about 500 miles.

638
02:01:26.364 --> 02:01:28.491
This is where your island was,

639
02:01:28.699 --> 02:01:31.702
about 600 miles south of the Cook Islands.

640
02:01:33.496 --> 02:01:35.748
And these are the search grids.

641
02:01:35.831 --> 02:01:39.168
Ships went back and forth for weeks looking for you.

642
02:01:47.468 --> 02:01:50.179
I never should've gotten on that plane.

643
02:01:52.098 --> 02:01:54.350
I never should've gotten out of the car.

644
02:01:58.479 --> 02:02:00.439
I wanna show you something.

645
02:02:02.525 --> 02:02:03.693
Come here.

646
02:02:13.953 --> 02:02:16.080
This is... This is our car.

647
02:02:18.416 --> 02:02:20.376
You kept our car.

648
02:02:22.545 --> 02:02:24.547
All right, now...

649
02:02:25.006 --> 02:02:26.507
This is weird.

650
02:02:34.265 --> 02:02:35.808
It's a good car.

651
02:02:36.434 --> 02:02:38.853
Had a lot of memories in this car.

652
02:02:38.936 --> 02:02:40.730
Two very nice memories.

653
02:02:41.605 --> 02:02:44.233
Oh, that trip down to the Gulf, yeah.

654
02:02:46.235 --> 02:02:47.945
So, can I drive it?

655
02:02:48.362 --> 02:02:49.905
It's your car.

656
02:02:58.039 --> 02:03:01.000
That's good, 'cause my... My taxi's gone.

657
02:03:09.592 --> 02:03:11.844
Let me get some stuff out of the back.

658
02:03:34.075 --> 02:03:36.577
You think you're gonna have more kids?

659
02:03:36.660 --> 02:03:37.995
I don't know.

660
02:03:38.329 --> 02:03:40.748
It's kind of confusing right now.

661
02:03:41.624 --> 02:03:43.000
Well, you should.

662
02:03:44.168 --> 02:03:46.420
I mean, really, you should.

663
02:03:48.672 --> 02:03:49.673
I would.

664
02:03:52.676 --> 02:03:54.303
So, what now?

665
02:03:57.723 --> 02:03:59.183
I don't know.

666
02:04:02.269 --> 02:04:04.021
I really don't know.

667
02:04:16.700 --> 02:04:18.702
You said you'd be right back.

668
02:04:23.958 --> 02:04:25.751
I'm so sorry.

669
02:04:27.795 --> 02:04:29.004
Me, too.

670
02:05:39.116 --> 02:05:40.117
Chuck!

671
02:05:44.663 --> 02:05:45.706
Chuck!

672
02:05:47.291 --> 02:05:48.584
Chuck!

673
02:06:07.228 --> 02:06:09.438
I always knew you were alive.
I knew it.

674
02:06:11.190 --> 02:06:13.234
But everybody said I had to stop saying that,

675
02:06:13.317 --> 02:06:14.693
that I had to let you go.

676
02:06:16.820 --> 02:06:18.197
I love you.

677
02:06:20.115 --> 02:06:22.159
You're the love of my life.

678
02:06:24.328 --> 02:06:26.121
I love you, too, Kelly.

679
02:06:28.249 --> 02:06:29.833
More than you'll ever know.

680
02:07:30.769 --> 02:07:31.770
Chuck?

681
02:07:39.653 --> 02:07:41.405
You have to go home.

682
02:08:30.788 --> 02:08:36.543
We both had done the math, and Kelly added it all up.

683
02:08:39.296 --> 02:08:41.048
She knew she had to let me go.

684
02:08:41.131 --> 02:08:43.801
I added it up, knew that I'd...

685
02:08:45.677 --> 02:08:46.845
I'd lost her.

686
02:08:49.598 --> 02:08:52.393
'Cause I was never gonna get off that island.

687
02:08:54.645 --> 02:08:58.482
I was gonna die there, totally alone.

688
02:09:05.572 --> 02:09:09.034
I mean, I was gonna get sick or
I was gonna get injured or something.

689
02:09:12.746 --> 02:09:14.623
The only choice I had,

690
02:09:17.334 --> 02:09:19.753
the only thing I could control

691
02:09:21.755 --> 02:09:24.133
was when and how

692
02:09:25.426 --> 02:09:28.137
and where
that was gonna happen. So...

693
02:09:30.472 --> 02:09:32.141
I made a rope.

694
02:09:34.852 --> 02:09:37.688
And I went up to the summit to hang myself.

695
02:09:41.358 --> 02:09:43.360
But I had to test it, you know?

696
02:09:43.444 --> 02:09:45.863
Of course. You know me.

697
02:09:48.574 --> 02:09:53.704
And the weight of the log snapped the limb of the tree.

698
02:09:53.829 --> 02:09:58.292
So I couldn't even kill myself the way I wanted to.

699
02:09:58.375 --> 02:10:01.170
I had power over nothing.

700
02:10:10.012 --> 02:10:13.599
And that's when this feeling came
over me like a warm blanket.

701
02:10:17.644 --> 02:10:20.397
I knew, somehow,

702
02:10:22.191 --> 02:10:24.526
that I had to stay alive.

703
02:10:25.903 --> 02:10:27.237
Somehow.

704
02:10:28.947 --> 02:10:31.241
I had to keep breathing,

705
02:10:33.827 --> 02:10:36.580
even though there was no reason to hope.

706
02:10:37.998 --> 02:10:41.668
And all my logic said that
I would never see this place again.

707
02:10:46.590 --> 02:10:48.425
So that's what I did.

708
02:10:49.510 --> 02:10:50.969
I stayed alive.

709
02:10:52.137 --> 02:10:53.889
I kept breathing.

710
02:10:56.350 --> 02:10:58.685
Then one day that logic was proven all wrong,

711
02:10:58.769 --> 02:11:03.440
because the tide came in,

712
02:11:03.732 --> 02:11:05.609
gave me a sail.

713
02:11:09.905 --> 02:11:11.615
And now, here I am.

714
02:11:15.077 --> 02:11:19.164
I'm back in Memphis,

715
02:11:19.373 --> 02:11:21.291
talking to you.

716
02:11:22.876 --> 02:11:24.795
I have ice in my glass.

717
02:11:32.010 --> 02:11:34.388
And I've lost her all over again.

718
02:11:42.229 --> 02:11:44.690
I'm so sad that I don't have Kelly.

719
02:11:49.903 --> 02:11:53.740
But I'm so grateful that she was with me on that island.

720
02:12:00.289 --> 02:12:02.833
And I know what I have to do now.

721
02:12:05.586 --> 02:12:07.504
I gotta keep breathing.

722
02:12:10.173 --> 02:12:12.676
Because tomorrow, the sun will rise.

723
02:12:13.844 --> 02:12:16.096
Who knows what the tide could bring?

724
02:13:22.162 --> 02:13:23.330
Hello!

725
02:13:28.377 --> 02:13:29.378
Hello!

726
02:13:38.053 --> 02:13:39.221
FedEx!

727
02:14:47.831 --> 02:14:49.082
You look lost.

728
02:14:49.583 --> 02:14:50.584
I do?

729
02:14:51.626 --> 02:14:53.003
Where are you headed?

730
02:14:57.048 --> 02:14:58.925
Well, I was just about to figure that out.

731
02:15:00.510 --> 02:15:01.887
Well, that's 83 South.

732
02:15:02.679 --> 02:15:05.807
And this road here will hook you up
with I-40 East.

733
02:15:07.350 --> 02:15:10.937
If you turn right, that'll take you to

734
02:15:11.021 --> 02:15:14.566
Amarillo, Flagstaff, California.

735
02:15:17.152 --> 02:15:19.780
And if you head back that direction,
you'll find a whole lot of nothing

736
02:15:19.863 --> 02:15:21.615
all the way to Canada.

737
02:15:24.284 --> 02:15:25.535
I got it.

738
02:15:26.161 --> 02:15:27.537
All right, then.

739
02:15:30.540 --> 02:15:32.042
Good luck, cowboy.

740
02:15:32.793 --> 02:15:33.919
Thank you.

